DNA analyses and discussion.
A 589 bp segment of the 16 S, 658 bp segment of COI and 689 bp segment of 28 S, from 55 species of fiddler crabs, were amplified and aligned (
Table 1
). The phylogenetic tree of the combined markers was reconstructed from the BI analysis, with the support values from two methods of ML analyses (
Fig. 9
). To estimate the divergence time, the substitution rate of 1.17 % / 10 6 year for the combined 16 S and COI of marine sesarmids (cf.
Schubart et al. 1998
;
Ragionieri et al. 2009
) was applied to the p-distance between clades.
